  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And when she looked, behold, the king stood by a pillar, as the manner was,.... Of kings, when they came into the temple on any occasion, civil or religious, therefore it is called his pillar, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 23:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", some think this was the brazen scaffold erected by Solomon, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 6:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", though Vitringa (e) and Bishop Patrick suppose it to be the post of the east gate of the inner court, from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 46:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", according to Jacob Leo (f), this was the royal throne in the court of the Israelites, near the high or upper gate, on a marble pillar, where the kings of the house of David sat, when they came into the sanctuary to see the Lord in the second temple; this throne was like an high tower, standing upon two pillars, each twenty cubits high, and their circumference twelve; here sat Joash, and Hezekiah, and Josiah; however, Athaliah saw Jehoash with the crown on his head, and in the place where kings used to sit or stand: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the princes and the trumpeters by the king; the rulers of the courses of the priests, and the Levites, blowing the trumpets: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and all the people of the land rejoiced, and blew with trumpets; it is added, in 2 Chronicles 23:13 that the singers played also on musical instruments; that were then and there assembled: ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and all the people of the land rejoiced, and blew with trumpets; it is added, in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 23:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " that the singers played also on musical instruments; that were then and there assembled: ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and Athaliah rent her clothes; through grief, and as one almost distracted: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and cried, treason, treason! to try if she could get any to take her part, and seize on the new king, and those that set him up. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(e) Proleghom. de Synagog. Vet. c. 4. p. 32. (f) Apud Wagenseil. Sotah, p. 680. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(e) Proleghom. de Synagog. Vet. c. 4. p. 32. (f) Apud Wagenseil. Sotah, p. 680. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
